Interface Aggregator.Parser

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPercentilesParser, AbstractTermsParser, AbstractValuesSourceParser, AbstractValuesSourceParser.AnyValuesSourceParser, AbstractValuesSourceParser.BytesValuesSourceParser, AbstractValuesSourceParser.GeoPointValuesSourceParser, AbstractValuesSourceParser.NumericValuesSourceParser, AvgParser, CardinalityParser, DateHistogramParser, DateRangeParser, DiversifiedSamplerParser, ExtendedStatsParser, GeoBoundsParser, GeoCentroidParser, GeoDistanceParser, GeoHashGridParser, HistogramParser, IpRangeParser, MaxParser, MinParser, MissingParser, PercentileRanksParser, PercentilesParser, RangeParser, SignificantTermsParser, StatsParser, SumParser, TermsParser, ValueCountParser

    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface Aggregator.Parser
    Parses the aggregation request and creates the appropriate aggregator factory for it.

    • Method Detail

      • parse

        AggregationBuilder parse(java.lang.String aggregationName,
                         QueryParseContext context)
                  throws java.io.IOException
        Returns the aggregator factory with which this parser is associated, may return null indicating the aggregation should be skipped (e.g. when trying to aggregate on unmapped fields).
        Parameters:
        aggregationName - The name of the aggregation
        context - The parse context
        Returns:
        The resolved aggregator factory or null in case the aggregation should be skipped
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - When parsing fails
